	(text "- VDD has 7 capacitors because:\n    - 3 VDD pins\n    - 2 VDDIO3 pins\n    - 2 VDDIO4 pins\n- VDDCORE has 6 capacitors because:\n    - 5 VDDCORE pins\n    - 1 VDDCSI pin\n- VDDA1V8 has 4 capacitors because:\n\n- Power input to board is 5V @ 3A max\n- Total of 5 LDOs and Bucks for 3v3 and 1v8\n    - Buck converter for 1v8 VDD, always on\n    - LDO for 1v8 VDDA18AON, always on\n    - LDO for 3v3 VDD3V3 (USB pin)\n    - LDO for 1v8 VDDA1V8\n    - LDO for 1v8 VDD1V8\n- All LDO's and Bucks should be adjustable\n   and with enable pins. Permanently enable\n   VDD and VDDA18AON\n\n- Ferrite bead (FB1) requirements:\n    - 50 Ohms at 100MHz\n    - At least 400mA I_DC\n    - Max 0.1 Ohms DCR\n\n- VREFP is reference for internal ADC.\n   J1 is a jumper to VDDA1V8, use separate\n   reference if desired.\n\n- Forgot to add in symbols:\n    - LDO's are SPX5205-ADJ\n    - Buck is MC34064-ACD-TR\n    - Schottky diode is 1A 40V per the\n       datasheet\n    - Ferrite will be ILB1206ER500V"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 231.14 25.4 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "83de9875-f306-42e9-bb4f-e92159b3454e")
	)
	(text "Design Notes"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 231.648 21.082 0)
